doc.after: The majority of Swaziland s population is ethnically Swazi mixed with a small number of Zulu and White Africans mostly people of British and Afrikaner descent Traditionally Swazi have been subsistence farmers and herders but most now mix such activities with work in the growing urban formal economy and in government Some Swazi work in the mines in South Africa
